hands_on_practices.problem:
Let $X$ and $Y$ be two continuous random variables. Their joint probability density function (PDF) is given by
$$
f(x,y) =
\begin{cases}
x+y & \text{for } 0 \le x \le 1 \text{ and } 0 \le y \le 1 \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$
Calculate the Pearson correlation coefficient, $\rho(X,Y)$, between the random variables $X$ and $Y$. Express your answer as a single closed-form analytic expression.
